    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nhi folks, currently when the title of a float win is longer than the window width, it gets truncated from the right side, and this behavior suprises me, because from my past experience, &winbar and tabpage title in &tabline truncate the text from the left side.\r\n\r\nmy usecase is that: i have a file browser plugin that shows files under a directory in a float window, and i name the title of that window using the absolute path of that directory. that's said the right most part of the path is most important to me.\r\n![0e22cc52-f15c-11ed-b934-54b203702c9c](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/6236829/20f46bf7-feee-4f39-ac13-056d75498bc3)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\ni surely can handle this by myself by cheking the length of title and window's width, but i think it's still worth to consider making nvim be consistent across its UI.\r\n\r\n(i asked this in the matrix room weeks ago, and got answered from glepnir, but i failed to find an issue that tracks other thoughts on this, sorry if there is one already)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\na over long float window title gets truncated from the left side",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I am not sure what is the best way to handle this. How do we guarantee the integrity of the title string. it is different in different situation. If pure truncation doesn't make any sense. For example your title string is a path\r\n` title = '/Users/foo/bar/dev/test/main.c`  . float win width is `16` . how to truncate ? result most right is  `ev/test/main.c`. \r\nleft is  `/Users/foo/bar/d` .. looks wired",
